  "prompt": "What hotel in Jowai Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "Ensuring a safe and comfortable stay for unmarried couples in India can be influenced by several factors including local cultural norms and policies of individual establishments. Here are some general tips to find a hotel in Jowai Hill-station that can be welcoming for unmarried couples:\n\n1. **OYO Rooms & Other Chain Hotels**: OYO Rooms generally have a policy that allows unmarried couples to stay without hassle. They often have the 'Couple Friendly' tag on their listings, and some other chains may follow similar policies.\n\n2. **Reviews and Ratings**: Look for hotels with positive reviews from other unmarried couples. Websites like TripAdvisor, Booking.com, and Google Reviews can be very helpful.\n\n3. **Direct Inquiry**: Call the hotel directly and ask about their policy regarding unmarried couples. Clear communication will often ensure you don\u2019t face any unwanted trouble.\n\n4. **Privacy and Security**: Choose more reputable or higher-end hotels as they usually prioritize guest privacy and security.\n\n5. **Online Booking Platforms**: Use platforms like MakeMyTrip, Goibibo, or Agoda which might have filters for couple-friendly stays.\n\nHere are a few options that could potentially be safe for unmarried couples:\n\n### 1. OYO Rooms:\n- Look for OYO properties explicitly marked as \u2018Couple Friendly\u2019. \n\n### 2. Couple Friendly Hotels through Booking Platforms:\n- **The Courtyard Guest House** - Check current policies and reviews.\n- **Nguni Residency** - Call and confirm their policies directly.\n\n### 3. Homestays or Airbnb:\n- Check if local homestays or Airbnb options can offer a couple-friendly environment.\n\n### 4. Hill Resorts:\n- Some high-end resorts may also be accommodating and provide a safe environment for all guests. \n\nAlways ensure to carry valid ID proof like Aadhaar card, driving license, or passport which will be required during check-in.\n\nRemember to verify current information directly from the property to avoid any inconveniences.",
